osis and hepatitis (n\u2009=\u200912, 16.9%), and white pulp depletion in the spleen (n\u2009=\u20097/71, 9.8%). Regarding emergent bat viruses, only poxvirus (n\u2009=\u20092, 2.8%) and orthoreovirus (n\u2009=\u200912/71, 16.9%) were detected in a low percentage of bats.\nConclusions\u2002 Trauma is the main lesion observed in bats collected in Turin province (North-western Italy) associated with forelimb fractures and the detected viral positivity rate seems to suggest that they did not represent a threat for human health.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Colombino, Elena", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Lelli, Davide", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Canziani, Sabrina", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Quaranta, Giuseppe", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Guidetti, Cristina", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Leopardi, Stefania", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Robetto, Serena", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "De Benedictis, Paola", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Orusa, Riccardo", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Mauthe Von Degerfeld, Mitzy", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Capucchio, Maria Teresa", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/86d4342e5b68973c19833fa271f2a5f9", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/a0db1a0d1dd82d1ceb6282c98bdfb6111b7cf8158092357bc1578f4a4c87903d", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/8Q7LWIEH", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/8Q7LWIEH", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/399f3384f9a43a7d687f04f1ca16e694!/b270050-272617", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/ce1e7618f237ff56e74d51f496e811a3", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "ur